<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="eggersiana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea eggersiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forms a species pair with 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="steudelii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. steudelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the two species differing only in their corolla shape, colour (crimson in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="steudelii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. steudelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, pink in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="eggersiana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. eggersiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and distribution. The corolla of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="eggersiana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. eggersiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is funnel-shaped, whereas that of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="steudelii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. steudelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is hypocrateriform with exserted stamens.
</paragraph>
